# nyne-refactor — Renames, Moves & Interface Changes

Refactoring through nyne's VFS reduces tool calls by an order of magnitude. The key
mechanisms: scoped reads eliminate wasted tokens, rich reference files provide all caller
context in one read, and diff-first mutations let bulk changes apply in a single command.

## MANDATORY: Before Any Refactoring

1. **Read `{{ FILE_CALLERS }}`** — understand who depends on what you're changing.
2. **Read `{{ FILE_REFERENCES }}`** — find all usage sites (especially for types/traits).
3. **Preview diffs before applying** — `cat rename/new_name.diff` or `cat actions/10-fix.diff`.

## Core Principle: Diff-First Mutations

Every mutation the VFS can perform is previewable as a `.diff` file. **Always preview
before applying** — this is the default workflow, not the alternative.

| Operation | Preview (read first) | Apply |
|-|-|-|
| Symbol rename | `cat {{ paths.sym_rename("file." ~ ext, "Foo", "new_name") }}` | `rm {{ paths.sym_rename("file." ~ ext, "Foo", "new_name") }}` |
| Code action | `cat {{ paths.sym_action("file." ~ ext, "Foo", "10-fix") }}` | `rm {{ paths.sym_action("file." ~ ext, "Foo", "10-fix") }}` |
| Batch edit (single file) | `cat {{ paths.edit_staged_diff() }}` | `rm {{ paths.edit_staged_diff() }}` |
| Cross-file batch | `cat {{ paths.edit_staged_diff() }}` | `rm {{ paths.edit_staged_diff() }}` |
| Direct rename | — | `mv {{ paths.sym_dir("file." ~ ext, "old") }} {{ paths.sym_dir("file." ~ ext, "new") }}` |

All preview paths are lookup-only (generated on read, not listed in `readdir`).

