## Workflow: Change a Function Signature (Interface Change)

This is the highest-value workflow — turns 24 tool calls into 4.

### Step 1: Read callers first (MANDATORY)

```sh
cat {{ paths.sym_md("src/lib." ~ ext, "process", "CALLERS") }}
```

Understand every call site before changing the interface.

### Step 2: Read and edit the function body (scoped)

```sh
cat {{ paths.sym("src/lib." ~ ext, "process", ext) }}          # ~25 lines, not 400
```

### Step 3: Write the new signature

```sh
# Write just the signature — body untouched
echo 'pub fn process(input: &str, timeout: Duration) -> Result<()>' \
  > {{ paths.sym_signature("src/lib." ~ ext, "process", ext) }}
```

### Step 4: Fix callers

**Option A — Check and apply code action diffs:**

```sh
# See what auto-fixes are available
ls {{ paths.sym_actions("src/lib." ~ ext, "process") }}

# Preview a fix
cat {{ paths.sym_action("src/lib." ~ ext, "process", "10-fix") }}

# Apply a fix (delete the diff to apply)
rm {{ paths.sym_action("src/lib." ~ ext, "process", "10-fix") }}
```

**Option B — Edit callers through symlinks:**

```sh
Edit src/lib.{{ ext }}@/symbols/process@/callers/init.{{ ext }}
  old_string: "process(input)"
  new_string: "process(input, timeout)"
```

### Step 5: Edit the function body

```sh
Edit {{ paths.sym("src/lib." ~ ext, "process", ext) }}
  old_string: "client.send(request)?"
  new_string: "client.send_timeout(request, timeout)?"
```

**Total: ~4-5 tool calls. ~725 tokens consumed.**

## Refactoring-Specific Anti-Patterns

| Anti-pattern | Correct approach |
|-|-|
| Grep for callers, read each file, edit each file | Read `{{ FILE_CALLERS }}` → edit through symlinks or apply diffs |
| `cargo check` after every edit | `cat {{ paths.file_diagnostics("file." ~ ext) }}` — instant |
| Manual find-and-replace for rename | Preview: `cat rename/new.diff`, then `rm` or `mv` |
| Reading full files to find call sites | `{{ FILE_CALLERS }}` has inline code context |
| Modifying a function without checking callers | **Always** read `{{ FILE_CALLERS }}` first |

